</html>
```

Next, we'll add some basic CSS to style our application. This will help us create a visually appealing design. Here's a simple example:

```css
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    background-color: #f4f4f9;
}

header, footer {
    background-color: #333;
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1em 0;
}

main {
    padding: 2em;
}

section {
    margin-bottom: 2em;
}
```

Finally, let's add some JavaScript to make our application interactive. This will allow us to create dynamic and engaging user experiences. Here's a simple example:

```javascript
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const button = document.getElementById('interactive-button');
    button.addEventListener('click', () => {
        alert('Button clicked!');
    });
});
```

By following these steps, you can build a simple web application that incorporates HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Remember, the key is to start with the basics and gradually expand your skills. Keep practicing and experimenting, and you'll be well on your way to creating more complex and engaging web applications. Good luck, and enjoy the process!
